to take such action as it sees fit, including terminating this Agreement or any other agreement in place with the User and/or taking legal action against such User.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>9.2. You agree to indemnify and hold harmless SuperPad, its affiliates, subsidiaries, licensors, and their respective directors, officers, members, managers, employees, and agents from and against any and all claims and expenses arising out of your use of the Services, a breach of any provision of these Terms by you or any person using the Services on your behalf, a breach by you of any applicable laws, or any third-party claim to the extent arising from or connected with an allegation that your use of the Services in accordance with these Terms infringes any rights of a third party.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>10. Force Majeure</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SuperPad shall have no liability for delays, failure in performance, or interruption of service which result directly or indirectly from any cause or condition beyond our reasonable control, including but not limited to, any delay or failure due to any act of God, the act of civil or military authorities, the act of terrorists, civil disturbance, war, strike or other labor dispute, fire, interruption in telecommunications or Internet services or network provider services, failure of equipment and/or software, other catastrophe or any other occurrence which is beyond our reasonable control and shall not affect the validity and enforceability of any remaining provisions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>9.2. You agree to indemnify and hold harmless SuperPad, its affiliates, subsidiaries, licensors, and their respective directors, officers, members, managers, employees, and agents from and against any and all claims and expenses arising out of your use of the Services, a breach of any provision of these Terms by you or any person using the Services on your behalf, a breach by you of any applicable laws, or any third-party claim to the extent arising from or connected with an allegation that your use of the Services in accordance with these Terms infringes any rights of a third party.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>11. Miscellaneous</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>11.1.&nbsp;Severability: If a provision of this Agreement is or becomes illegal, invalid, or unenforceable in any jurisdiction, that shall not affect the validity or enforceability in that jurisdiction of any other provision hereof or the validity or enforceability in other jurisdictions of that or any other provision hereof.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>11.2.&nbsp;Assignment: SuperPad reserves the right to assign this Agreement, in whole or in part, at any time without notice. The User may not assign any of his/her rights or obligations under this Agreement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>11.3.&nbsp;Third-Party Rights: Unless expressly provided to the contrary in this Agreement, a person who is not a party to this Agreement has no right to enforce or to enjoy the benefit of any term of this Agreement. Notwithstanding any term of this Agreement, no consent of any party who is not a party to this Agreement shall be required for the waiver, variation, or termination of any part of this Agreement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>11.4.&nbsp;Support and Notice: All notices, requests, demands, and determinations for SuperPad under these Terms (other than routine operational communications) shall be sent to [Support@superpad.finance].</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>12. Severability</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If a provision of this Agreement is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable in any jurisdiction, that shall not affect the validity or enforceability in that jurisdiction of any other provision hereof or the validity or enforceability in other jurisdictions of that or any other provision hereof.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>13. Assignment</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SuperPad reserves the right to assign this agreement, in whole or in part, at any time without notice. The User may not assign any of his/her rights or obligations under this Agreement.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<h2>14. <strong>Cryptocurrency</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cryptocurrency values can fluctuate greatly in value depending on market condtions.</li>\r\n	<li>The user Warrants that it is aware of the volatile nature of cryptocurrencies and holds superpad harmless for any loss or damages arising from such volatility.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'SuperPad - Terms And Conditions', 'SuperPad - Terms And Conditions', 'term-and-condition', 1, 'Help', '2022-03-20 14:48:48', '2022-03-26 13:56:55'),
(7, 'Cookies', '<h3><strong>Cookies</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>In this Cookies Policy, we explain what cookies and/or similar technologies (collectively; &quot;<strong>Cookies</strong>&quot;) are, what they are used for, and how you can configure or disable them. In addition, we provide you with information about the types of Cookies, and their purposes, used on this &quot;Website&quot; owned by SuperPad.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&zwj;<strong>1. What are Cookies and what are they used for? &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&zwj;</strong>Cookies are technologies that allow the storage and retrieval of information when you browse the Website. They can serve a variety of purposes, such as, for example, recognizing you as a user, obtaining information about your browsing habits, or customizing the way in which content is displayed. The specific uses we make of Cookies are described below.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&zwj;<strong>2. What types of Cookies are there?<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&zwj;</strong>Below we provide a classification of Cookies according to a series of categories. Please note that the same Cookie may be included in more than one category.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2.1. Types of cookies according to the entity that manages them<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFirst-party cookies: are those that are sent to your computer from the website managed by SuperPad.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThird-party cookies: are those that are sent to your computer from a computer and/or domain that is not managed by SuperPad, but by another entity that uses the data obtained through cookies for its own purposes.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2.2. Types of cookies according to the length of time they remain active on your device<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSession Cookies: are those designed to collect and store information only for the duration of your visit to the Web Site, and disappear at the end of the session. They are normally used to store information that you are only interested in keeping to ensure the basic functionalities of the Web Site during your visit to it.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPersistent Cookies: are those in which the information obtained remains stored in the terminal and can be accessed and processed for a period longer than the duration of your visit to the Website, which is defined by the person responsible for the Cookie. This period varies according to each Cookie, and can range from a few minutes to several years.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2.3. Types of cookies according to their purpose<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSession cookies: are those that allow you to browse the Website. Session cookies will allow you to use the different functionalities and services of the Website, for example the login with your identifier.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nUtility or personalization cookies: are those that allow you to remember information so that you can access the Website with features that can differentiate your experience from those of other users, such as, for example, the appearance or content of the Website, which may vary depending on the type of browser you use.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAnalysis or measurement cookies: are those that allow the monitoring and analysis of your behavior on the Website. This information makes it possible to measure and analyze the use of the Website, (techniques as well as to elaborate user browsing profiles, with the aim of introducing the necessary improvements to the Website based on the analysis of the browsing data collected.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAdvertising Cookies: are those that allow the management, in the most efficient way possible, of the advertising spaces that, where appropriate, have been included in the SuperPad website.Behavioral advertising cookies: are those that allow the effective management of advertising spaces that may have been included on the Website, through the storage of information on your behavior obtained through the continuous observation of your browsing habits, which allows the development of a specific profile to display advertising based on the same.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&zwj;<strong>3. What Cookies does SuperPad</strong><strong> use on the Website?<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&zwj;</strong>This Web Site uses Cookies that store and retrieve information when you browse. &nbsp;Below, we explain what Cookies we use, as well as their characteristics and purposes.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nYou can accept or reject the use of cookies through the cookie settings center that VENT makes available to you, which you can access either through the basic cookie information message that appears at the beginning when you visit the Website for the first time, or through the following link, which will direct you to the cookie settings center: Cookie Settings.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn the SuperPad cookie settings center you can consent to the use of cookies, as well as withdraw any consent to their use already granted, at any time and as many times as you wish.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPlease note that if you accept third-party cookies, you should delete them, if you wish, directly through your browser&#39;s cookie management options, as explained in the following section 4.2.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n4.2. Cookie configuration through your browser<br />\r\n<br />\r\nYou can allow, block or delete cookies installed on your computer at any time through the options made available to you by the browser you use. Please note that if you disable all cookies, some features or content of the SuperPad website may be affected. We tell you how to do it:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you use&nbsp;<strong>Microsoft Internet Explorer</strong>: click on the Tools button in Internet Explorer and then on Internet Options &gt; Privacy &gt; Settings &gt; OK. For more information, click&nbsp;<a href=\"https://support.microsoft.com/es-es/help/17442/windows-internet-explorer-delete-manage-cookies\" target=\"_blank\">here<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&zwj;</a>If you use&nbsp;<strong>Firefox</strong>: click on the Firefox button and select Options &gt; Privacy &gt; Use custom settings for history &gt; Check the Accept cookies option to enable them, and uncheck it to disable them &gt; Choose how long cookies will be stored &gt; OK. For more information, click&nbsp;<a href=\"https://support.mozilla.org/es/products/firefox/privacy-and-security\" target=\"_blank\">here<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&zwj;</a>If you use&nbsp;<strong>Chrome</strong>: click on the Chrome menu in the browser toolbar &gt; Settings &gt; Show advanced options &gt; In the &quot;Privacy&quot; section, click on Content settings &gt; In the &quot;Cookies&quot; section, you can configure cookies. For more information, click&nbsp;<a href=\"https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647?hl=es\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you use&nbsp;<strong>Safari</strong>: go to Preferences and, in the Privacy panel, choose Block Cookies, and select the option you prefer from those offered by the browser. For more information, click&nbsp;<a href=\"https://support.apple.com/es-es/guide/safari/sfri11471/mac\" target=\"_blank\">here<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&zwj;</a>If you use&nbsp;<strong>Opera</strong>: click on Settings &gt; Options &gt; Advanced &gt; Cookies. For more information, click&nbsp;<a href=\"https://help.opera.com/en/latest/web-preferences/#cookies\" target=\"_blank\">here<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&zwj;</a>If you are using an&nbsp;<strong>iPhone or iPad</strong>: from the home screen, select Settings &gt; Safari and then choose your preferred settings option. For more information, click&nbsp;<a href=\"https://support.apple.com/es-es/HT201265\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you are using&nbsp;<strong>Android</strong>: click on Menu &gt; Settings &gt; Security &amp; Privacy &gt; check or uncheck the &quot;Accept cookies&quot; box &gt; Restart the browser for the changes to take effect.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you are using&nbsp;<strong>Windows Phone</strong>: in Internet Explorer, click on More &gt; Settings. You can also access Internet Explorer settings through Settings in the list of applications. Select or deactivate the option Allow cookies.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>5. Additional Information</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nYou can consult additional information about the treatment of your information, in particular about your rights and the modalities of exercising them, in the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.vent.finance/legal#privacy-policy\">Privacy Policy</a>&nbsp;of SuperPad, which we invite you to consult.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCookie Policy last update: 06-03-2022</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'SuperPad - Cookies', 'SuperPad - Cookies', 'cookies', 1, 'Help', '2022-03-25 14:45:37', '2022-03-26 13:56:34');

